      <h1 class='title'>Anti-terrorism, Crime and Security Act 2001:Report on Part IV</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='lords-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 11 February 2004 vol 656 cc49-50WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_49ws' title='Col. 49WS &mdash; HL Deb 11 February 2004 vol 656 c49WS' name='column_49ws' href='#column_49ws' rel='bookmark'>49WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0656P0-06695'>
        <a name='S5LV0656P0_20040211_LWS_1'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-patricia-scotland' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0656P0_20040211_LWS_1' title='Link to this speech by Ms Patricia Scotland' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-patricia-scotland" title="Ms Patricia Scotland">The Minister of State, Home Office (Baroness Scotland of Asthal)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S5LV0656P0-06695">Lord Carlile of Berriew has completed the report on the operation of Part IV of the<a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_50ws' title='Col. 50WS &mdash; HL Deb 11 February 2004 vol 656 c50WS' name='column_50ws' href='#column_50ws' rel='bookmark'>50WS</a>
          <a href="/acts/anti-terrorism-crime-and-security-act-2001">Anti-terrorism, Crime and Security Act 2001</a>, in 2003, which will be laid before the House today.</p><p id="S5LV0656P0-06696">We are grateful to Lord Carlile for his work and I am pleased to note that he is again satisfied that my right honourable friend the Home Secretary has certified persons only in appropriate cases and that he has exercised his independent judgment in each case having given due regard to advice from officials.</p><p id="S5LV0656P0-06697">We welcome Lord Carlile's recommendations, which we will be considering in detail over the next few weeks. They will provide a useful contribution to the debates.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
